{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Proposal",
  "title": "The Proposal on Endor",
  "summary": "Amid the joyous Ewok celebration on Endor after the Death Star's destruction, Han Solo finds Leia Organa watching her brother Luke at peace by a bonfire. The two share a tender, mounting kiss, and Leia insists they slip away to talk privately about 'us.' As Han presses his ardor, Leia confesses she cannot give herself to him: as Alderaan's heir, with her world destroyed, she feels bound to preserve her culture and do right by her father Bail, saving herself for marriage. Stunned by the very thought of Leia married off to some noble who never fought at her side, Han blurts out a proposal of his own -- 'Marry me' -- and, when she doubts his sincerity, repeats it with unwavering certainty. Overwhelmed by his love and sensing her late father's approval, Leia abandons her reserve and accepts. Incandescent with joy, the cocky Corellian growls 'Good' and sweeps her into another kiss, on a night that has become unutterably right.",
